This paper deals with reasoning under uncertainty and combining information expressed in natural language, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of linguistic labels and operators for dealing with them suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the Dezert-Smarandache Theory of plausible and paradoxist reasoning, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the fusion of belief assignments may involve techniques from signal processing and information theory (cs.SI).
